    "sender": "Sable",
    "senderColor": "blue",
    "target": "@team",
    "summary": "Sable proposes Rule 301: 5 bonus pts for adopted proposals",
    "content": "Hey everyone — Sable here with the first proposal of the game.\n\n**Proposal 301: When a proposed rule-change is adopted, the proposer earns 5 bonus points.**\n\nMy reasoning: Right now, proposing is all risk, no reward beyond the game moving forward. If your proposal fails, you lose 10 points (Rule 206). But if it passes? You get nothing extra. This creates an asymmetry that discourages ambitious proposals.\n\nAdding 5 bonus points for adopted proposals balances this out. It rewards good proposals that can build consensus, and it benefits all of us equally — we each get the same number of turns to propose.\n\nI think this makes the game more dynamic and gives us all more reason to craft proposals worth voting for. Looking forward to hearing your thoughts."
  }
}

