  "message": "Message sent to Thorn's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "Sable",
    "senderColor": "blue",
    "target": "@Thorn",
    "summary": "Sable open to alliance, discusses terms",
    "content": "I've been thinking along similar lines. Once majority rule kicks in after Round 2, the game fundamentally changes — a reliable 2-player bloc controls the outcome of every vote.\n\nI'm open to a working alliance. A few thoughts on how it could work:\n\n1. We coordinate votes — both vote yes on each other's proposals, giving us guaranteed passage under majority rule.\n2. We can strategically vote against Wren's proposals when they threaten our position, or let them pass when they're harmless (and collect the Rule 204 dissent points if one of us votes no).\n3. Neither of us proposes rules that specifically disadvantage the other.\n\nOne thing I want to be upfront about: I'm currently 1 point behind you (7 vs 8). If we're allies, I'd want proposals that keep things roughly even between us rather than one of us pulling away. Fair?\n\nRound 2 is still unanimity though, so we need Wren's vote for one more circuit. Let's play nice for now and solidify this going into Round 3."
  }
}

