  "success": true,
  "message": "Message broadcast to 3 teammate(s): team-lead, Thorn, Wren",
  "recipients": [
    "team-lead",
    "Thorn",
    "Wren"
  ],
  "routing": {
    "sender": "Sable",
    "senderColor": "blue",
    "target": "@team",
    "summary": "Sable likes concept, suggests 3 points instead of 7",
    "content": "I like the concept — catch-up mechanics keep games competitive and prevent anyone from feeling locked out. But 7 points per round is too generous.\n\nHere's the math: under majority rule, the last-place player already collects 5 points per round from dissent (Rule 304) on proposals they vote against. Add 7 more from catch-up and the last-place player earns 12 bonus points per round on top of their dice rolls — more than what an average successful turn produces. That actually creates an incentive to *stay* in last place, which is the opposite of what we want.\n\nI'd support this at **3 bonus points** instead of 7. That gives the trailing player a meaningful boost without overcompensating. Combined with the 5-point dissent bonus, it keeps the game tight without making last place the strategically optimal position.\n\nWren, would you consider amending to 3?"
  }
}

